node.text: I thought this would be cool for you to see. Acting has been my only purpose. To be able to connect with fictional and non fictional characters on the deepest level possible has been the most rewarding experience I could’ve ever imagined. We are all a product of conditioning. Once we remove ourselves from those conditionings, any emotion is possible. People ask me, “How is it possible that you can cry on command? How do you do it?” and my only response is, this is not mechanical. Emotions are not mechanical. If you start to manipulate emotions as an actor, you are removing yourself from the truth. An actors job is to bring life to the roles we are given, not deliver dialogue. The dialogue is already written, the audience doesn’t want to see the dialogue recited to them. They want to feel and believe. I love monologues because they are the best practice for me and I film most of them because I like to dig deeper into each moment and learn from each piece. Fun fact, comedy isn’t my strongest suit. I wear it proudly, but I am excited for you to see the projects that I am working on that will truly show my strengths as a performer. Love Christian❤️

node.text: Today is the day we remember and honor all of the brave heroes who served to hold our flag high. To all the soldiers who made the ultimate sacrifice for this country, thank you for your service. Sending love to all the families of the fallen. #memorialday

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by christian delgrosso on May 24, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: Today is my damn BIRTHDAY! This time last year I spent my birthday alone without @kristenmcgowan due to COVID which was extremely hard on me. I hadn’t seen Kristen through the entire year of 2020 and my only wish was that we would get to be together again! Fast forward another year which feels like 4 days ago, I have Kristen sitting next to me, I am SO happy, and we get to spend our birthdays with each other this week! To end on one of my favourite quotes “We don’t stop playing because we grow old, we grow old because we stop playing”. Every year that goes by and I grow older, I remember to not let age hinder my ability to have a young mind! Cheers, to forever growing young! Love you all and thank you for everything you’ve done for me❤️
